  <!-- ========== FAQ ========== -->
  <section class="section faq-section" id="faq" aria-label="Frequently asked questions about beauty salon AI search optimisation in Singapore">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header reveal">
        <p class="section-label">FAQ</p>
        <h2>Beauty Salon AI Search Optimisation — Questions Answered</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d1">
          <summary>How do beauty clients find salons through AI?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Clients ask ChatGPT, Gemini, and Perplexity questions like "best facial treatment in Singapore" or "Korean hair salon near Orchard." AI platforms evaluate review quality, treatment-specific content, and authority signals to recommend 3-4 salons per query. Salons without optimised AI signals don't appear in these recommendations.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d2">
          <summary>Why isn't my Google ranking enough for AI visibility?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>The overlap between Google rankings and AI citations has dropped below 20%. A strong Google presence no longer guarantees ChatGPT or Gemini will recommend your salon. AI models evaluate different signals — review sentiment, structured data, content authority, and third-party mentions — to decide which salons to name.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d3">
          <summary>Which AI platforms recommend beauty salons in Singapore?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>ChatGPT, Google Gemini, Google AI Overviews, Perplexity, and Microsoft Copilot all answer beauty service queries. Each platform pulls from different data sources, so we optimise your salon's presence across all of them to capture every client searching via AI.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d1">
